title: Murray Sunset Np South Flora South Of Sturt Hwy

items.title: Haloragis odontocarpa f. pterocarpa
items.content_text: A few leaves seen throughout the NW at this time but only this plant with buds.

items.title: Halgania cyanea
items.content_text: One white among many blue-flowered plants.

items.title: Acacia nyssophylla
items.content_text: 20ish veins and gland well above leaf base distinguish this from A. colletioides.

items.title: Cynoglossum australe
items.content_text: Mericarps with barbed spines, inflorescence ebracteate.

items.title: Ptilotus nobilis subsp. nobilis, Waitzia acuminata var. acumi...
Kippistia suaedifolia
items.content_text: Masses at this location but only 100m or so either side, then nothing.

items.title: Maireana radiata
items.content_text: Small, appressed leaves on cottony stems. On pic2 the start of radiating veins just visible.

items.title: Boronia coerulescens subsp. coerulescens, Laevicampsomeris fo...
items.content_text: Wasp flying exclusively to Blue Boronia plants. Watched it for a few minutes.

items.title: Calytrix spp.
items.content_text: Awnless sepals and other features suggest C. alpestris but C. tetragona found nearby (see 10885) and alpestris not quite recorded in Murray-Sunset NP.

items.title: Pimelea trichostachya
items.content_text: Podotheca angustifolia in the background of pic 2.

items.title: Hyalosperma spp.
items.content_text: Either H. semisterile or H. glutinosum, most likely the former. Need fruit for ID. Location approximate.

items.title: Podolepis rugata var. rugata
items.content_text: Just make out the wrinkly/pleated bracts. Location approximate.

items.title: Triodia scariosa
items.content_text: A ring of plants- a formation this species often makes. Location approximate.

items.title: Pterostylis mutica
items.content_text: Can't see it can be anything else? Location approximate.

items.title: Trachymene cyanopetala
items.content_text: 3-6 fruit per umbel but not the usual bluish tinge. Location approximate.

items.title: Castiarina spp., Waitzia acuminata var. acuminata
Phebalium bullatum
items.content_text: Almost completely buried in sand but still flowering. Approximate location.

items.title: Calytrix tetragona
items.content_text: Almost buried in the sand. Approximate location.

items.title: Eremophila glabra subsp. murrayana
items.content_text: The fight for survival. Approximate location.

items.title: Olearia rudis
items.content_text: Only appears after fire. Approximate location.

items.title: Eremophila glabra subsp. murrayana
items.content_text: Growing among Waitzia acuminata. Approximate location.

items.title: Glischrocaryon behrii
items.content_text: 2nd pic shows mass display with Waitzia acuminata. Approximate location.

items.title: Eremophila glabra subsp. murrayana
items.content_text: Low, almost prostrate. Quite hairy this sample. Approximate location.

items.title: Maireana radiata
items.content_text: 2nd pic shows radiating veins from the centre of the fruit. Approximate location.

items.title: Maireana pentatropis
items.content_text: Zooming in you can just make out the hairy centre of the fruit. Approximate location.

items.title: Senecio spanomerus
items.content_text: Approximate location. Much debate over this one but weight of evidence suggests it is most likely S. spanomerus (not S. pinnatifolius var. pinnatifolius).

items.title: Calotis cymbacantha
items.content_text: Leaf shape is a distinguishing feature. Approximate location.

items.title: Brachyscome ciliaris var. brachyglossa
items.content_text: Note much-reduced ligules (petals) on this variety. Approximate location.

items.title: Podolepis rugata var. rugata
items.content_text: 2nd pic shows ID feature of the pleated bracts. Approximate location.

items.title: Ptilotus spathulatus
items.content_text: Shows creeping stems well. Approximate location.

items.title: Podolepis capillaris
items.content_text: Plant is almost invisible when not in flower. Waitzia acuminata in the back ground. 2nd pic by Doug Down. Approximate location.

items.title: Harmsiodoxa blennodioides
items.content_text: Fruit in 2nd pic is the key ID feature.

items.title: Zygophyllum simile
items.content_text: Not recorded anywhere near Pink Lakes previously. Small white flower top-right of pic shows 8 stamens, making it Z. simile.
